Common String Operations and Methods:
Concatenation:
Combining two strings together.
  
str1 = "Hello"
str2 = "World"
result = str1 + " " + str2
print(result)  # Output: Hello World


Length:
Finding the length of a string.
 
my_string = "Python"
length = len(my_string)
print(length)  # Output: 6


Indexing and Slicing:
Accessing individual characters or a range of characters in a string.
  
my_string = "Hello"
print(my_string[0])    # Output: H
print(my_string[1:3])  # Output: el


Conversion:
Converting a string to lowercase or uppercase.
 
my_string = "Hello"
print(my_string.lower())  # Output: hello
print(my_string.upper())  # Output: HELLO


Stripping:
Removing leading and trailing whitespaces.
 
my_string = "   Hello   "
stripped_string = my_string.strip()
print(stripped_string)  # Output: Hello
